Anh - Anh
herringbone
■ noun
1》 a pattern consisting of columns of short parallel lines, with all the lines in one column sloping one way and all the lines in the next column sloping the other way.
    ⁃ a cross stitch with a pattern resembling this.
2》 Skiing a method of ascending a slope by walking with the skis pointing outwards.
■ verb
1》 mark with a herringbone pattern.
    ⁃ work with a herringbone stitch.
2》 Skiing ascend a slope using the herringbone technique.

sentences.en: Those would go well with a herringbone suit.
sentences.vi: Những cái đó sẽ rất hợp với một bộ quần áo may bằng vải chéo chữ chi.

sentences.en: Herringbone floors has been a long time traditional floor pattern in Europe.
sentences.vi: Sàn nhà kiểu hình chữ chi là kiểu sàn truyền thống từ rất lâu ở châu Âu.
